It's not perfect, and people are going to bitch no matter what solution is tried. I for one would vote for us to keep a centralized reservation system for the older planes, and the major dragons (Vox, Nagy and Trak). Perhaps tweak them somewhat to help allievate the congestion and bickering, but the same general principle is a good one. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujonduval.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jonduval</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/22/01 11:34:25 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.fastlane.net/~kurtis/wow/jonduval12x20.jpg width=120 height=200></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Not happy? Make a change!</span><hr size=1> Ariannda is promoting a <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.showMessage?topicID=5861.topic">guild meeting</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> in chat for Wednesday night. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uminutemanaslayer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Minute Manaslayer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 467<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/23/01 12:06:51 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Not happy? Make a change!</span><hr size=1> Aye, what I put up was an extremely fast attempt to hold our server from splitting into chaos.  I do not proclaim it to be the all out answer.  It is just another way.  I don't make the decisions for the server.  The servers people make the decisions.  YOU ALL make the decisions.  I'm more then happy to maintain the site in the interest of our community.  I'm also more then happy to work on something else.  All that is important is that we do infact maintain, because anything else is chaotic.<br>
<br>
The meeting is a great idea, provided that its done efficiently without any bias or favor.  As always I am willing to adhere to what the majority of the community wishes because I do not place my ideas and values over the majority of people.<br>
<br>
We Must Maintain<br>
<br>
Minute Manaslayer<br>
57th Sage Charmer<br>
Realm Brell Serilis <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubrinklith.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brinklith</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://http://www.aelf.net/pics/10x10s.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Jester of Avalon</span><br>  Posts: 287<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/23/01 12:41:32 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.aelf.net/pics/brink-now.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Not happy? Make a change!</span><hr size=1> My suggestion is to leave the VS rotation in-place until the crashes are clear and we can see what effect the increased spawn is having before making any rash decisions. The Brave New World of FCFS raised its ugly head on Sunday after the server crash: &quot;we're here for VS and @#%$ the rest of you&quot;.<br>
<br>
As far as other reservations go, my vote is for keeping all of them that currently exist, including a list on Fire Giants. The only people who still want FG loot are those that are young enough to need a multi-group raid. Everyone older has a better alternative from Kunark or Velious. I don't see why a group that is strong enough to do FGs in a single group would WANT to do it. There must be better exp and loot elsewhere?<br>
<br>
Finally, I know I'm not the only one that thinks this way. The suggestion is that Delsonora should take some time off. He's had offers from many people to help out which have been refused, and the past few days have seen a marked sea change in the Mods' policies. I know there were problems with rants (and the police) and your decision there is respected, but that's no excuse for your other actions on this board: deleting signatures, editing posts and taking decisions based on a quick &quot;this is right, isn't it&quot; question to representatives of three guilds. This isn't &quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Oh the usual recycled Kruunch trash..</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot; (quote: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub65.ezboard.com/fbrellserilis13167frm1.showMessage?topicID=11.topic">pub65.ezboard.com/fbrells...D=11.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> ). I have abslutely no affiliation with any guilds on this server. Either hand over to someone else permanently, or at least walk away from the board for a week or two: you've got too close.<br>
<br>
Still, since it appears any views contrary to the board admin's are seen as flames, I doubt this post will have any effect. If you're going to ban me for dissent Delsonora, don't bother banning the IP address: it's dynamic AND several other Brell members use the same ISP (including my girlfriend).  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufuffette.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fuffette</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/23/01 1:27:09 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Idea to help</span><hr size=1> If we were to have each guild appoint a representative to act on the behalf of their guild in votes and other issues this would certainly cut down on some of this totally unnecessary slander Del is forced to endure.  This in no way means I agree or disagree with any decision made by the Mod's but I do feel that if there were reps for each guild and they each had input that the issue of VS and/or calandar issues for instance would not be so out of hand.  There are so many issues that need to be dealt with and it is impossible for a handful of people &lt;mods&gt; to do this without controversy.  Therefore I feel a representative from each guild could rectify allot of the headaches Del is suffering from.<br>
<br>
A council of Guilds if you will.  Perhaps this will also allow the &quot;Uber&quot; Guilds to get to know some of the &quot;Smaller&quot; Guilds as well <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I am also at your service I am willing to assist in any way to preserve the civilized server we call Brell <br>
<br>
<br>
Fuffette Lostalot<br>
